-- Hungary Stocks: OTP, FHB Bank, Magyar Telekom Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-02-24T16:23:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/hungary-stocks-otp-fhb-bank-magyar-telekom-move-in-budapest.html
Hungary ’s benchmark BUX stock index
gained 1.6 percent to 19,372.48 as of the close in Budapest. The
following are among the most active equities in the Hungarian
market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, rose 3.3
percent to 4,040 forint. Hungary’s retail sales increased 1.5
percent in December compared with a year earlier, exceeding
economists’ estimates in a Bloomberg survey.  Foldhitel es Jelzalogbank Nyrt.  (FHB HB), a Hungarian
mortgage lender, increased 6.9 percent to 543 forint. The lender
bought back covered mortgage bonds and European bank stocks
advanced.  Magyar Telekom Nyrt. (MTEL)  , Hungary’s former phone
monopoly, climbed 0.9 percent to 591 forint in a third day of
gains. The company announced a dividend after its 2011 earnings
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
